@@TJvBalloonHint.OnMouseUp
Summary
  Occurs when the user releases a mouse button that was pressed with the mouse pointer over a balloon
  hint.
Description
  Use an OnMouseUp event handler to implement special processing when the user releases a mouse
  button.
  
  The OnMouseUp event handler can respond to left, right, or center mouse button presses and shift
  key plus mouse-button combinations. Shift keys are the Shift, Ctrl, and Alt keys. X and Y are the
  pixel coordinates of the mouse pointer in the client area of the Sender.
  Note
  This event does <I>not</I> occur for application hint windows, only for balloon hints launched with
  a call to ActivateHint, ActivateHintRect etc.
See Also
  TJvBalloonHint.OnBalloonClick, TJvBalloonHint.OnMouseDown

