@@TJvBalloonHint.OnMouseMove
Summary
  Occurs when the user moves the mouse pointer while the mouse pointer is over a balloon hint.
Description
  Use the OnMouseMove event handler to respond when the mouse pointer moves after the balloon hint
  has captured the mouse.
  
  Use the Shift parameter of the OnMouseMove event handler, to determine to the state of the shift
  keys and mouse buttons. Shift keys are the Shift, Ctrl, and Alt keys or shift key-mouse button
  combinations. X and Y are pixel coordinates of the new location of the mouse pointer in the client
  area of the Sender.
  Note
  This event does <I>not</I> occur for application hint windows, only for balloon hints launched with
  a call to ActivateHint, ActivateHintRect etc.
See Also
  TJvBalloonHint.OnMouseDown, TJvBalloonHint.OnMouseUp

